HEADWORD: Semester
<hw>Se*mes"ter</hw> <pr>(s⟦esl⟧*m⟦ecr⟧s"t⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[G., from L. <ets>semestris</ets> half-yearly; <ets>sex</ets> six +
<ets>mensis</ets> a month.]</ety> <def>A period of six months;
especially, a term in a college or university which divides the year
into two terms.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

